{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
*NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-6299].
{panel}
As a customer, I'd like to have the option to have a different banner image for each portal (project). Currently, the banner set is applied to all the projects in the help center.

h3. Summary

Add new comment to a service desk issue:

REST API v2:
{code:java}
{
	"body": "Anne this is commentt",
	"jsdPublic": false
}
{code}
V3:
{code:java}
{
    "body": ""{
        "type": "doc",
    "version": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Anne this is comment",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]"",
    "jsdPublic": false
    }
}
{code}
does not hide the comment:
 !Snip20190311_10.png|thumbnail! !Snip20190311_11.png|thumbnail!
h3. Workaround

Use JSD Create request comment REST API: [https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/service-desk/rest/#api-rest-servicedeskapi-request-issueIdOrKey-comment-post.]
